SIMPLE: molecule
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Molecule
<hw>Mol"e*cule</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Dim. fr. L.
<ets>moles</ets> a mass: cf. F. <ets>mol⟦eacute⟧cule</ets>. See 3d
<er>Mole</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One of the very small invisible
particles of which all ordinary matter is supposed to consist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>The smallest part of any
substance which possesses the characteristic properties and qualities of
that substance, and which can exist alone in a free state.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A group of atoms so united and
combined by chemical affinity that they form a complete, integrated
whole, being the smallest portion of any particular compound that can
exist in a free state; <as>as, a <ex>molecule</ex> of water consists of
two atoms of hydrogen and one of oxygen</as>. Cf.
<er>Atom</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mole-eyed</ent>⟦br⟧
